<br>
I have every piece i wear hot-keyed on my front page, although the gloves and bracer get swapped in only when i'm grouped(actually, i'll have gloves in there every once inawhile when soloing).  I never use regular snare when soloing, its just alot more convenient knowing your ensnare will last 10 minutes rather than 2 i believe.  The 2 minute snare is fine for most of my grouping sessions.  I believe the boots have a faster cast time than the actual spell, not 100% sure but feels like it, and i almost always have lev up when soloing.  The bracer is nice for group situations although i have to tell the people that want to bash to move away so it doesnt override the SOW i put on them.  Alot of people i group with in KC prefer Wolfform over SOW mostly cuz of the attack bonus, but other classes enjoy being a wolf so they can make some wolf emotes.  Some people even say it gives them a haste effect or faster mana/hp regen but i dont really buy that.  The arms speak for themselves and i use those every chance i get.<br>
<br>
All in all i really like ES armor but i like all armor that has right click effects.  I'm currently working on a full suit of effect armor.  I've always thought Druids put too much of an emphasis on wisdom, unless your quading or kiting alot.  Dont think many people kite these days with the implementation of root stacking with snare, but i cant remember how effective our dots were at earlier lvls so i might be wrong about Druids kiting(single mob kiting, not quading) these days.  Heres how the prices are generally on these pieces on Fennin Ro...<br>
<br>
ES bp - 80k<br>
<br>
ES legs - 60k(hard to find a seller in my exp)<br>
<br>
ES arms - 3k<br>
<br>
ES bracer - 2k<br>
<br>
ES Boots - 3-10k(varies, but hard to find in my exp)<br>
<br>
ES helm - 3k(seen people try and sell for 10k or so, but 3k is fair for helm)<br>
<br>
Imo, the arms are a must-have for any druid at 45 or higher.  The helm becomes obsolete once you get improved sup camo.  The bp is nice cuz it has wisdom and is uber, but imo the chloro effect is slightly overrated cuz of group chloro and just not worth the 80k imo.  The legs are invaluable cuz its a mana free heal.  The boots are nice if your like me and keep lev up most of the time.  The bracer and gloves are convenient, but far from a necessity.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushanarwolfinator.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShanarWolfinator</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 10:48:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3182.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elder Spiritist's Questions</span><hr size=1> If you want AC on the gloves go with Coldain skin...it has 12ac AND a bunch of other good stats, 9sta 6int/wis 20mana/hp.<br>
